    <body>
      <head>Marianne Elisabeth Oppel</head>
      <div>

        <p>Daughter of <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard Oppel</ref> and his third wife <ref
            cRef="entity-008529">Käthe (<hi rend="italic">née</hi> Eggeling)</ref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>Marianne was the daughter – and sixth child – of <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard
            Oppel</ref> and the first child of his third wife <ref cRef="entity-008529">Käthe (<hi
              rend="italic">née</hi> Eggeling)</ref>. By the time that Marianne was born, her <ref
            cRef="entity-008529">mother</ref> had apparently left the marriage and returned from
            <ref cRef="entity-002757">Kiel</ref> to St Peter Ording (a town on the northwest coast
          of Schleswig-Holstein, 100km (80 miles) west of <ref cRef="entity-002757">Kiel</ref>).
          Marianne is never mentioned in <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard</ref>’s correspondence
          with either Heinrich or <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette</ref> Schenker, and it is
          questionable whether she ever had any practical place in his life.</p>
      </div>

